The InternationalAssociation of Machinists and Aerospace Workers said checkstotaling 33 mln dlrs are being mailed to 2,500 of its memberswho formerly worked for Republic Airlines and are now employedby Northwest Airlines (NWA).    The payoffs result from a trust agreement and employeestock ownership plan negotiated in early 1984 by the union toprotect Republic workers when the airline was in financialdifficulty, the union said.    Republic has since merged with Northwest Airlines. Reuter&#3;